Auftrag ID: 1066260219

*Env* : IT

*Actual Result:* Contract summary and contract documents are not reflected in IT OneDMS.

*Expected Result:* Contract summary and contract documents should be visible successfully in OneDMS.

column38:
Placing order with combination of "GigaZuhause CableMax 1000 + Kabel TV" but 
Wunschtermin auswahlen there is no dropdown and right side dates not able to select.

*Steps to Re-produce:*

1) Login to OSF Telesales Channel ACC1

2) Search with Unity Media serviceability address (Ex: Laubenweg 2 59821 Arnsberg)

3) Select KIP + TV product ( Ex: GigaZuhause CableMax 1000 + Vodafone TV Connect Zuhause)

4) Do check out and proceed the order

5) Under Lieferoptionen option check *"Wunschtermin auswahlen"* dropdown have option to select *Datum Lieferung and* right side date selection available.

 

*Actual Result: "Wunschtermin auswahlen"* dropdown no option to select *Datum Lieferung and* right side date selection not possible.

*Expected Result:* Lieferoptionen option  *"Wunschtermin auswahlen"* dropdown have option to select *Datum Lieferung and* right side date selection available.
column197: Date not able to select
column442: Solved with CR794 delivery CN_19083 from TechM
column747:
13/Jan/25 3:26 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;After discussion with TechM it seems there is some misunderstanding.

-----------------

TechM: 

The purpose of the CR is to have same delivery details(delivery address + delivery date) if we have multiple Cable packages in the order.

System will show the UI of capture delivery method details only for first package and for the rest of the cable packages in the order it will show the package name only.

There are no changes on wish date, it will remain as is

-------------

Earlier we had this CR but it got removed from Software and probably therefore we do not see any other values in the dropdown for the wish date for UM

[OAF-598] CR794 - UM: Desired Delivery Date ("Lieferoption Wunschtermin") - Vodafone Global Jira

Checking with Nora and Thorsten;;;

column1: OSF | Wave 9.1.1 | ACC1/2/3 | FN GetProductAvailability failing with VFP-00005 error for 'ONKZ_QUERY' parameter
column38:
*Issue description:*

getting below error while doing customer search

*Error in VFP response:* Pflichtparameter (abhängig): Wenn der Parameter 'PHONE_NUMBER_EXISTING_CUSTOMER' angegeben ist, muss der Parameter 'ONKZ_QUERY' ebenfalls angeben werden.

 

Use case: Existing customer Fixnet shows availability GLAS/DSL/LTE as grey although the address itself is having the availability

*Test Data:* customer no. 1926427263

*Steps to reproduce:*

1.Login to Retail/Telesales channel

2. Do legacy customer using customer no.

3. check  getresponse in logs

Problem – Error Code

Output for FN GetProductAvailability : <xml-fragment>
<ResultCode>VFP-00005</ResultCode>
*<ResultText>Pflichtparameter (abhängig): Wenn der Parameter 'PHONE_NUMBER_EXISTING_CUSTOMER' angegeben ist, muss der Parameter 'ONKZ_QUERY' ebenfalls angeben werden.</ResultText>*
<NumberHits>0</NumberHits>
</xml-fragment>

It seems OGW is missing to send areaCode to Backend and therefore we are getting this error.

Specification (very old)
|ONKZ_QUERY|Conditionally|0[1-9][0-9]+|Area code for the ASB-Suche with leading '0' (e.g. '069').
Mandatory, when one of the parameter CITY and PLZ in the object VFP_ADDRESS_QUERY is empty.
Mandatory, if the parameter PHONE_NUMBER_EXISTING_CUSTOMER in the object O_VFP_EXISTING_CUSTOMER_QUERY is passed.|

 

There have been ACC/ SIT tickets in 2018 for the same and it got fixed by OGW but the tickets are too old to find (Z_PRT00089777A/ PRT00088105A)

 

 

Its already present in production seems like last week, but I did not find an amdocs fix which went live on 11{^}th{^} of November, which could have caused it.

07/Jan/25 7:02 PM;alka.kshirsagar2@vodafone.com;Mail from Maro:

 

Hi all,

 

concerning the logic of providing the parameter in the service availability call for existing customers:
 # If a TASI exist for the customer this one has to be provided (which works currently)
 # If no TASI is found (which is the case for all LTE customers) the existing phone number has to be send -> to be provided as phonenumber

           2.1 And in addition the ONKZ value -> to be provided as areaCode

 

The part 2.1 seems to be missing

 

During the first waves we had the discussion how the parameters should be filled

 

Please check if the parameter is already missing in Omnius or only on OGW side.

 

Regards,

Marco

column38:
*Only tracking Bug- new change from Amdocs to delete the DSL Barcode IDs from MOB&CAB stack is required* (Rohan)

 

We are testing the functionality of CR 804 and observed that Barcode are not getting generate for Cable and Mobile in retail channel 

Ref Link:  [https://jira.sp.vodafone.com/browse/FAST-801]

Omnius ID: 454891

OGW ID: 30047771

Mobile ILS:

Omnius ID: 454795

OGW ID: 30047639

column442: adding new barcode check for cr804
column747:
26/Nov/24 3:43 PM;ran.farjun1@vodafone.com;Hi,
Following the implementation of the new Barcode CR, the router SOS functionality is not working correctly.
 
Before the CR, the barcode contained the ogwOrderId, which allowed the router to identify the environment to which the order belongs.
 
After the CR, the barcode no longer includes the ogwOrderId, preventing the router from determining the correct environment for the order.;;;
column748:
27/Nov/24 7:15 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;We have discussed about two possible solutions

1) Full solution -> needs full deployment to all ACC environments, and more complex implementation

2) Patch for ACC1 and ACC2, which ensures that status with new sequence is routed directly to ACC3 and ignoring ACC1, ACC2

For now, second option is preffered to not impact ACC1, ACC2 that much and to have fast solution. Ran is going to prepare relevant patches

Around 5th of February we need permanent full solution for all ACC; once CR804 is going to be merged on ACC1, ACC2 as well. This needs to be organized and monitored ;;;

column1: OSF | WAVE 9.1.2 | ACC3 | "Kunde mit Vollmacht"  Skip reason is not visible in Telesales channel
column38:
Note:

This is only a tracking Bug, it will not impact the scope of CR860, as CR860 is related to Retail channel. Planned to be delivered in upcoming release.

 

 

 

We observe that "Kunde mit Vollmacht"  Skip reason is not visible in Telesales channel if we are skipping MTAN 

 

*Steps to Reproduce:*

1)Login to ACC3-Telesales with a user who has a role where the permission "MTAN+20FX" is assigned
2)Search for Mobile Private customer
3)details will be visible in masked format 
4)retrieve customer
5)MTAN window will be visible 
6)Skip reason "Kunde mit Vollmacht"

*Expected Result:* "Kunde mit Vollmacht"  Skip reason Should be visible in Telesales channel

*Actual Result:* "Kunde mit Vollmacht"  Skip reason is not visible in Telesales channel
h3.
column197:
When skipping mTAN, agent will not see the new skip reason  "Kunde mit Vollmacht" in TS. 
No business impact, because the reason is not relevant for TS channel, only technically the restriction to RT is not possible.

22/Oct/24 6:05 PM;ariadne.thun1@vodafone.com;Summary of Discussion with ADBA Team
DB Size
Observed that ITROMDB is significantly larger than PRROMDB. Despite the size difference,there is no noticeable impact on performance.

DB Configuration
Compared the configurations, both databases have identical configurations, including software versions and patches.

SGA (System Global Area) 
Compared SGA components such as shared pool, buffer cache, and redo log buffer, including their sizes and configurations. All components are  same in both database.

Gather Stats Status for Specific Tables
Checked statistics gathering status for tables OM_REPORTING_IN, OM_REQUEST,EA_REQUEST,OM_REQUEST,OM_ORDER,OMS_RENDERRESULT,OM_REPORTING_OUT and OM_ORDER. Include details on when stats were last gathered and their current status. All table stats are up to date and no table found in stale_stats status

Check for Abnormalities in ITROM Database
Identify any abnormalities in the ITROM database, such as performance issues, error logs and unusual behavior.-->In progress, ADBA Team will provide details soon. ADBA team will highlight if any abnormalities found

 

Analyze AWR Report
Provide a brief summary of the AWR report, including the time period covered and any significant findings-->In progress, ADBA Team will provide details.

Analyze Enqueue and Dequeue Processes and Queue Tables
Any abnormalities in enqueue and dequeue processes including any specific queue tables used-->In progress, ADBA Team will provide details soon.;;;

column1: OSF | ACC3 | Wave 8.2.3 | Regression | Service Address check with Auto suggestion is not working as expected
column38:
While performing Service availability check we are unable to perform the service check with the auto suggestion.

where previously we able to search with this format -- - 81927 Munchen gottfried 15 ---

and address search was working but

now since tuesday 14th May we have to enter addresses in detail -- 81927 munchen gottfried-benn-str. 15 

 

And if we are missing any single character to add we get error "No Address Found"

 

Steps to Reproduce:

1) Login to Telesales/ Retail and perform Service availability check

2) enter address in format : 81927 - Munchen- Gottfried- 15 this will give error  and 

using this format 81927 - Munchen - Gottfried-benn-str.-15 this will work 

 

Expected Result:

Only entering 81927 - Munchen- Gottfried- 15 should also give the result of address without auto suggestion.

 

Actual Result:

currently we have to use the detailed address to search the same. and if we are missing any single character we are getting error as "NO Address Found"
column197: Address check is not working as expected due auto suggestion issue

column1: OSF | ACC3 | ON HOLD Wave 8.1 | IMPROVEMENT CR to fix DSL Telesales orders are getting stuck at OnHold-PendingDSLShop
column38:
While performing today sanity we observed that DSL telesales orders are stuck at state OnHold-PendingDSLShop. so that orders are not getting submitted to backend. {color:#de350b}*This is only for ACC3*{color}

*Steps to reproduce:*

Login to Omnius Telesales channel

Select DSL Product

Proceed to checkout

Submit order

Track order in OGW

 

*Expected Result:*

Order confirmation by DSL shop should came from Tivano/Eshop

Order should submit to BE 

 

Test data : 
Order id :  428201  , Barcode : VDE5600000076

Order id : 428193  , Barcode: VDE5600000058
column197: DSL Orders are not getting submitted to backend in case we are changing the sequence on OGW side for OGW order ID
column442: delivery of CR804
column747:
25/Oct/23 12:14 PM;rohan.kumbhar@vodafone.com;Defect to be kept ON-HOLD-- currently here the issue is that OGW is creating a BARCODE which can accept max 8 digits where the new sequence id which is changed for OGW order is is having 9 digits due to which when OGW is trying to search customer is CDM it counts the 8 digits starting from RHS where the last digit is ignored 
So in this case the new order id = 900000073 where while searching it is only calculating 73 ignoring all the 0 digits as they are null.
The last 9 digit =9 is been not counted at all as it only does counting until 8 digits which is 00000073 

To adapt these changes --we need to have a CR in OGW to implement the changes;;;
